[SN]TITLE[SN]
Euro 2016 countdown:: Mark Hughes' winner sees Wales beat England in 1984

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
As Wales and England prepare for Euro 2016, we remember when Mark Hughes' debut goal in 1984 earned Wales their third win over England in seven years.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is not supported on this device
The Manchester United youngster's header just 17 minutes into his international debut proved the difference at the Racecourse as Wales won 1-0.
This game in Wrexham in May 1984 would prove to be the final Home Nations Championship meeting.
